Cross-Account S3 Copy – Task Breakdown
#	Task	Account	Why It Is Needed (Business View)	Ideal Owner
1	Create IAM Role for cross-account access	PROD	Create a controlled, temporary access mechanism instead of giving permanent access	Cloud Platform / AWS Infra Team
2	Define IAM Policy (Read-only access to specific S3 bucket)	PROD	Ensure only required data can be read (no delete or modify permissions)	Cloud Platform / Security
3	Configure Trust Policy (allow NON-PROD role to assume role)	PROD	Restrict who can borrow the temporary access badge	Cloud Platform
4	Update PROD S3 Bucket Policy	PROD	Explicitly allow secure read access from NON-PROD role	Cloud Platform
5	Update PROD KMS Key Policy (Allow Decrypt)	PROD	Allow encrypted files to be securely opened for copying	Cloud Platform + Security
6	Create/Use IAM Role to perform copy operation	NON-PROD	Define which system/service performs the copy	DevOps Team
7	Grant sts:AssumeRole permission	NON-PROD	Allow NON-PROD role to temporarily access PROD role	Cloud Platform
8	Configure NON-PROD S3 Bucket Policy (Allow Write)	NON-PROD	Ensure data can be stored securely in destination bucket	Cloud Platform
9	Update NON-PROD KMS Policy (Allow Encrypt, if used)	NON-PROD	Ensure copied data remains encrypted in NON-PROD	Cloud Platform + Security
10	Execute Data Copy (aws s3 sync / automation job)	NON-PROD	Perform actual transfer of data	DevOps Team
11	Validate Data Integrity & Access	NON-PROD	Confirm successful transfer and usability	DevOps + Application Team
12	Enable Monitoring & Logging (CloudTrail)	Both	Ensure audit and compliance visibility	Cloud Platform / Security
13	Remove or Restrict Access After Completion (if one-time task)	Both	Reduce long-term security exposure	Cloud Platform
